706093f-a.text:
Nostrand Ave., south from Ave. T. This view has not changed in recent years. The country is sparsely settled. It required three years to have it extended from Ave. Q, to Ave. U., a distance of about 5 blocks.
March 22, 1927.
E. E. Rutter Company.
706093f-a.folder: Nostrand Avenue & Avenue T, Brooklyn, NY

707023f-b.text:
(1)
ave. T, north side, between Nostrand ave., and Haring Street, showing at the right the home of J. Stillwell from 1857-1860, and of J.S. RUyder in 1873. This house is standing toeday (1929) and is at the N.W. corner of Haring Street and Nostrand Ave. The other house No. 2941 Ave. T, was designated (1916) as at the N.E. corner of Ryder Ave., and
Ave. T.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The samie, another view.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, looking south from Ave. S, along Ryder Ave. The house (at left) partially seen is No. 3303 Nostrand Ave. Judge
Nicholas Stillwell's house is in the background.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
